<li>Below we discuss these two functions as well as the possible role of nanH in the LexA regulon and concept of steric coupling to explain the downregulation of porphyrin-metabolism genes by MX .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17925033" target="_blank">17925033</a>]<br></li>
<li>LexA Regulon The LexA regulon encompasses an ensemble of genes involved in preserving cell viability under massive DNA damage and is present in most bacterial phyla [ Benson et al , 2000 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19598237" target="_blank">19598237</a>]<br></li>
